  <body>

    <div class="navbar navbar-fixed-top">
      <div class="navbar-inner">
        <div class="container-fluid">
          <a class="btn btn-navbar" data-target=".nav-collapse" data-toggle="collapse">
            <span class="icon-bar"></span>
            <span class="icon-bar"></span>
            <span class="icon-bar"></span>
          </a>
          <a class="brand" href="/"><i></i> TreeDee</a>
          <div class="container nav-collapse">
            <ul class="nav">              
              <li><a href="#aboutModal" data-toggle="modal">About</a></li>
              <li><a href="#glassesModal" data-toggle="modal">3D Glasses?</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div><!--/.nav-collapse -->
        </div>
        <div id="social-media">
          <%= yield :social_media %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="container" class="container-fluid">

      <div class="content">
              <%= yield %>
      </div><!--/content-->

    </div> <!-- /container -->

    <div id="aboutModal" class="modal hide fade in" style="display: none; ">  
      <div class="modal-header">  
        <a class="close" data-dismiss="modal">×</a>  
        <h3>About</h3>  
      </div>  
      <div class="modal-body">    
        <p>This site exists half way between the realm of humor and valuable learning exercises. 
          Thanks to the awesome friend who told me "do it" when I decided to share the joke one morning.</p>
        <p>Built on <a href="http://rubyonrails.org/">Rails</a>, <a href="http://threejs.org">three.js</a>, and <a href="http://rubygems.org/gems/mersh">mersh</a>.</p>
        <p>Long live <b>#VegasTech</b>!</p>
        <p style="text-align: right">-<a href="http://twitter.com/makenai">@makenai</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>  

    <div id="glassesModal" class="modal hide fade in" style="display: none; ">  
      <div class="modal-header">  
        <a class="close" data-dismiss="modal">×</a>  
        <h3>3D Glasses?</h3>  
      </div>  
      <div class="modal-body">    
        <p>To see 3D you're probably going to need a pair of red and blue 3D 
          glasses. The old kind. Like this: <img src="/assets/3d_glasses.png" alt="3D glasses" />.</p>
        <p>You can find some for free <a href="http://free-3d-glasses.com/">here</a> or.. (while 
          supplies last) you can send a self addressed stamped envelope to:</p>
        <p>Pawel Szymczykowski<br />
          2280 Corporate Circle #100<br />
          Henderson, NV 89074</p>
      </div>
    </div>  


